reviewText: My stepdaughter introduced me to this series, and I have to say not since Rocky and Bullwinkle have I seen a cartoon that both kids and adults can greatly enjoy and find humorous on their respective levels. All of the seasons of Spongebob are great, but in season two the series really hits its stride. My favorites include "Survival of the Idiots" in which Patrick and Spongebob get trapped in Sandy's treedome during her hibernation. The creator of this show has obviously befriended a Texan or two. Anyone who has owned or been owned by a cat will enjoy "Dumped" and "Gary Takes a Bath", both of which deal with Spongebob and Gary, his pet Snail. "Grandma's Kisses" has some of the most memorable quotes in which Patrick assures Spongebob that being a man consists of doing three things:Patrick: Allow me to demonstrate. First, puff out your chest.[SpongeBob puffs out his chest]Patrick: Now say, "tax exemption."SpongeBob: Tax exemption.Patrick: Now you must develop a taste for free-form jazz.In "Squidville" well-deserved fun is poked at the dull uniformity of planned communities and homeowners associations...Anyone who lives in the DC area knows EXACTLY what I am talking about! Another classic is "Bubble Buddy", in which Spongebob has an imaginary friend who has been causing problems around Bikini Bottom all day. In Squidward's case his tragedy is that Bubble Buddy "forced him to provide excellent customer service". Anybody out there who has worked for a living will recognize Squidward as the fellow employee who wants to do the required minimum because he believes he is somehow destined for greater things.In short, if you want something that both you and the kids can watch and truly enjoy together, you can't do any better than Spongebob.
summary: Great viewing for kids and adults

reviewText: SpongeBob season 2 is one of my favorite seasons. I have been watching SpongeBob since it come on air. SpongeBob Squarepants is a must have favorite to kids and adults alike. Here is the complete guide of season 2.Disc 11. Your Shoe's Untied. SpongeBob forgets how to tie his shoe.2. Squid's Day Off. Krabs left Squidward in charge of the Krusty Krab and Squidward become paranoid of SpongeBob when he left him alone in the joint.3.Something Smells. One of my favorites. Hungry for a snack, SpongeBob makes a sundae of ketchup and onions, then he gets bad breath which scares everyone in Bikini Bottom except Patrick.4. Bossy Boots. Pearl, Krabs' teen daughter gets the restaurant a makeover for teenagers, but disaster strikes for Pearl.5.Big Pink Loser. One of my favorites. Tired of begin a loser and jealous of SpongeBob's numerous awards, Patrick wants a trophy like SpongeBob and he will do whatever he wants to get one.6. Bubble Buddy. With no one to spend together, SpongeBob creates a bubble buddy which is a pain to the citizens of Bikini Bottom.7. Dying for Pie. During a tradition at the Krusty Krab, Squidward accidently gave SpongeBob a pie bomb and he spent their "final" hours together.8.  Imitation Krabs. Plankton imitates Krabs, so he can steal the secret krabby patty formula.9. Wormy. Sandy left SpongeBob and Patrick in charge of her pet worm and disaster strikes for them when they think a "evil" butterfly ate Wormy.10. Patty Hype. SpongeBob sells Pretty Patties.11. Grandma's Kisses. Embarrassed for kissing his grandma, SpongeBob decides that he wants to grow up, but it is too much for him.12.Squidville. Fed up with SpongeBob's and Patrick's childish antics again, Squidward decides to move in with his own kind.13.  Pre-Hibernation Week. Sandy has to burn her carbs before she hibernates in a week with SpongeBob.14. Life of Crime. SpongeBob and Patrick "steal" a balloon and they become fugitives.15. Christmas Who? A special episode which Patchy hosts. It is Christmas, SpongeBob decides to spread the holiday that the citizens of Bikini Bottom do not know after a visit with Sandy.Disc 216. Survival Of The  Idiots. While Sandy is  hibernating, SpongeBob and Patrick sneak inside the Treedome and they cause chaos inside.17. Dumped. Jealous of Patrick and Gary together, SpongeBob do whatever it takes to Gary to love him back.18. No Free Rides. Miss Puff "passes" SpongeBob of the boating exam, but she realizes that she made a mistake.19. I'm Your Biggest Fanatic. During a visit at a jellyfishing convection with Patrick, SpongeBob meets his favorite Jellyfisher.20. Mermaidman and Barnacleboy III. Introduction of ManRay. SpongeBob and Patrick housesit for their favorite heroes, but disaster strikes for them when they foolishly freed a villain.21. Squirrel Jokes. During comedy night, SpongeBob makes insensitive jokes about Sandy.22. Pressure. Sandy and SpongeBob compete who is the best creature in land or sea ?23. The Smoking Peanut. During a visit at the zoo with Patrick, a stressed out giant oyster's cries are loud enough to heard in the entire world and SpongeBob thinks he is to blame.24. Shanghaied. SpongeBob, Patrick, and Squidward sneak inside the Flying Dutchman's ship and the ghost enslaves them.25. Gary Takes a Bath. It is bath time for Gary, Gary refuses to take a bath and it is up to SpongeBob to make him take a bath.26. Welcome to the Chum Bucket. After losing at poker night against Plankton, SpongeBob has to work at the Chum Bucket.27. Frankendoodle. Disaster strikes after SpongeBob and Patrick found a pencil.28. The Secret Box. SpongeBob became curious about Patrick's secret box.29. Band Geeks. Introduction of Squidward's rival, Squilliam Fancyson. Squidward wants to impress his rival in the battle of the bands.Disc 330. The Graveyard Shaft. Krabs sets up a 24 hour shaft at the Krusty Krab.31. Krusty Love. Krabs develops a crush on Miss Puff and he kept spending his money for her love.32. Procrastination. SpongeBob has to write a 800 word essay and he kept goofing off.33. I'm With Stupid. SpongeBob helps Patrick impress his parents, but disaster strikes for SpongeBob.34. Sailor Mouth. One of my favorites. SpongeBob and Patrick learnt profanity from a dumpster.35. Artist Unknown. SpongeBob enrolls in Squidward's art class and Squidward is impressed with SpongeBob's art skills.36. Jellyfish Hunter. After SpongeBob adds jam to his krabby patty, Krabs sent SpongeBob to gather jellyfish and he can add jam on his krabby patties, so he can get more money.37. The Fry Cook Games. One of my favorites. SpongeBob and Patrick compete each other in the fry cook games.38.Sandy, SpongeBob and The Worm. My all time favorite. A monstrous worm is rampaging Bikini Bottom and it is up to Sandy and SpongeBob to save the day.39. Squid on Strike. SpongeBob and Squidward are on labor strike against Krabs.As a fan of SpongeBob, I gave the entire series 5 stars.

reviewText: I've always found SpongeBob a little bit smarter than most of the other kid shows out there. The difficulty in creating a Looney Tunes type show, is that there has to be the perfect balance of true wit and slapstick, so that the humor isn't too cynical for kids,  but keeps the parents engaged. LT managed this balance flawlessly, and I believe SpongeBob comes pretty close. Nothing will ever top or replace the masterpieces that Chuck Jones, Friz Freleng, and Texas Avery (to name a few) helped to create in the franchise. However, SB comes about as close as anyone is going to, in coupling wit and slapstick through animation, without erring on the side of stupidity or cynicism.

reviewText: Some of you out there may or may not have noticed that the quality of more recent episodes of SpongeBob SquarePants has been seriously deteriorating. It was a fantabulous cartoon at the start of its run and for its first few years on Nickelodeon, but it started to go downhill after the movie and lose its sparkle. I mean, it still can be funny, but not in the same way as the earlier episodes, and it has gained some extra stupidity to it along with the quality drop, I am sorry to say. (I have written some negative reviews for the later seasons, too, which I suggest checking out so you can see how things have started to worsen).However, Season 2 was a great season for SpongeBob, before the drop in quality. The episodes were witty, cute, and hilarious, and extremely nostalgic for longtime fans of SpongeBob SquarePants as well. This is why they would make a wonderful gift for any fan of SpongeBob SquarePants in your life who may not have them on DVD, video, et cetera. It would be a penny well spent!

reviewText: Fans of this program already know how fun and witty it is for both kids and adults.  Here's what we have to look forward to when this second season DVD finally comes out:1.  Something Smells / Bossy Boots:  SpongeBob gets bad breath from his sundae made of ketchup and onions.  Pearl gives the Krusty Krab--I mean, the Kuddly Krab--a makeover.2.  Your Shoe's Untied / Squid's Day Off: SpongeBob forgets how to tie his shoes.  Squidward is left in charge of the Krusty Krab and decides to leave early only to keep returning for fear of what SpongeBob might do.  In this episode, we see Squidward actually swimming in a bathtub, which is a very funny sight!3.  Big Pink Loser / Bubble Buddy: Patrick wants a trophy and decides to imitate award magnet SpongeBob.  SpongeBob makes a new friend that the rest of the town does not appreciate.4.  Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy III / Squirrel Jokes:  SpongeBob and Patrick foolishly unleash the evil ManRay. SpongeBob discovers that the only way to get laughs during his comedy act is to make fun of Sandy (this one is one of my favorites).5.  Christmas Who?: Patchy the Pirate hosts a half hour special where SpongeBob brings Christmas to Bikini Bottom.6.  Dying for Pie / Imitation Krabs: Squidward thinks he's given SpongeBob a fatal pie, and stays with him during his "last hours." Plankton masquerades as Mr. Krabs.7.  Wormy / Patty Hype: SpongeBob and Patrick take care of Sandy's pets and freak out when her worm is eaten by an evil butterfly-looking thing.  SpongeBob markets Pretty Patties.8.  Survival of the Idiots / Dumped: Sandy is hibernating, but that doesn't stop SpongeBob and Patrick from visiting.  Gary the Snail finds a new best buddy in Patrick, much to the chagrin of SpongeBob.9.  Grandma's Kisses / Squidville:  SpongeBob is teased for kissing his grandmother. Squidward finds a neighborhood more accommodating to his lifestyle.10.  No Free Rides / I'm Your Biggest Fanatic:  Mrs. Puff decides to pass SpongeBob no matter what.  SpongeBob hangs out with an expert Jellyfisher.11.  You Wish ("Shanghaied") / Gary Takes a Bath:  SpongeBob, Patrick, and Squidward get three wishes on the flying Dutchman's ship.  Someone ends up taking a bath...and it isn't Gary.12.  Pressure / The Smoking Peanut:  The gang starts up the old "whose better? land creatures or sea creatures?" debate.  Clamu is going through emotional distress.13.  Pre-Hibernation Week / Life of Crime:  Sandy has only one week to burn carbs before hibernating-can SpongeBob survive that long?  SpongeBob and Patrick become fugitives after stealing a balloon.14.  The Secret Box / Band Geeks:  Patrick has a secret box.  Squidward starts up a marching band to show up rival Squilliam.15.  Sailor Mouth / Artist Unknown:  My all-time favorite!  SpongeBob and Patrick learn some new words.  The greatest artist in his own mind, Squidward, is bettered by his pupil, SpongeBob.16.  Jellyfish Hunters / Fry Cook Games:  SpongeBob uses jellyfish jelly on his krabby patty which starts a new craze and is bad news for the jellyfish.  Just in time for the Olympics, well it would be if this DVD would come out sooner!  SpongeBob and Patrick compete in the fry cook games.17.  The Bully / Just One Bite:  SpongeBob encounters a new classmate who wants to kick his butt.  Another favorite of mine: Krabby patty-hating Squidward discovers what he has been missing in life.18.  Sandy, SpongeBob and the Worm / Squid on Strike:  An Alaskan Bullworm invades Bikini Bottom.  Squid takes on Mr. Krab's "house of servitude."19.  Procrastination / I'm With Stupid:  SpongeBob procrastinates on writing a paper.  SpongeBob pretends to be a moron to make Patrick look smart in front of his parents.Considering how long it is taking to get this season out on DVD, there should be lots of extras as in the First Season set.
summary: "If Nautical Nonsense Be Something You Wish. . ."

reviewText: This is a review of this product:SpongeBob SquarePants - The Complete 2nd Season DVD.  Amazon may display this review on the page of another version of this product, for which this review may not apply.  After reading this review, please click on the link so that you can be assurred that the product this review applies to is the same one you thought it was for.--------------------------------------------------How can this be a "complete" 2nd season when the two alternate versions of "Shanghaied" are missing? Paramount/Viacom/Nick included the Patrick and Squidward ending versions on the"Sea Stories" DVD, but yet left them out as bonus features on this set. I'd like to know why. Double-dipping, I suppose. They've done that with almost all of the 13 (as of this writing) unnecessary individual releases, some of which contain bonus materials not found on the season sets.Speaking of bonus materials, this set has very little of them, especially when compared to season 1. Since they already have a lot of bonus materials in the vault from the individual releases, it wouldn't have been a lot of trouble to include them in this set. Again, double-dipping, I guess, provides the answer.
summary: Not As "Complete" As It Should Be

reviewText: The 2nd season of SpongeBob was the first to be made in Digital ink-and-paint technology, and the rest of the whole series has been made that way, for the most part, ever since. But that doesn't mean a shortage of hilarious and landmark episodes, no matter how you buy this set, be it the bulky box or the new single case. This set contains the edited currently-seen print of You Wish, alias Shanghaied, called Patchy's Pick; but it's amazing the First 100 Episodes set has this unedited! It also contains one of my favorite Christmas classics not related to Rankin/Bass, Hanna Barbera, or Disney; The (original) SpongeBob Christmas Special, alias Christmas Who? This one marks the debut of Patchy the Pirate and Potty the Parrot, and it contained a certain gag about how Squidward acted toward SpongeBob on Christmas Morning. There's 18 other pairs of episodes in this landmark season, when SpongeBob was starting to bypass Rugrats' popularity; from SpongeBob's "ugliness" or peanut-onion sundae breath, to the debut of his Grandma, to Pantera's take on Sandy's extreme side, to the debut of Man Ray, to SpongeBob's popular-yet-misunderstood  Squirrel Jokes, to the Krusty Krab's first time being open 24 hours a day, to SpongeBob and Patrick learning about the 13 bad words, to the Fry Cook Games, to Sandy and SpongeBob's escapade with the Alaskan Bull Worm! There's a bunch of bonus features here, including non-expert commentaries from the crew at the time, and storyboard comparisons on a few episodes and how they compare to the final cuts. This also contains the unedited version of Procrastination, yet many of the episodes seem brighter in color here than being seen on TV, even today! There's a glitch in Something Smells that's in here and in The First 100 Episodes set; SpongeBob was supposed to say "Hi building", when the audio accidentally repeats "I just don't get it" and Patrick answering "I don't either." Don't ask me what happened, even the crew was baffled when doing a commentary for this episode. Make sure your SpongeBob season set collection isn't limited to only season 1; every season is worth looking into for a longtime fan of this show like me, just like with every season of both Digimon and Rugrats! (It's a shame Shout Factory doesn't have the home video rights for Rugrats OR its spin-off show All Grown Up, I checked; those kinds of sets would be even better and cheaper than the MOD-DVD sets by comparison!) With me, it's far better and cheaper to get season sets of all 3 of my all-time fave Nicktoons than to get single volume discs of them. Add season 2 of SpongeBob to your collection today, unless you've already done it a long time ago.
